## 7. No error handling or structured logging (A09 — Security Logging & Monitoring Failures) — **Medium**

`console.log` isn't sufficient and there is no central error handler. Unhandled errors will leak stack traces via Express's default error page.

```js
const pino = require('pino');
const logger = pino({ redact: ['req.headers.authorization', '*.password'] });

app.use((req, res, next) => {
  req.log = logger.child({ reqId: req.headers['x-request-id'] || crypto.randomUUID() });
  next();
});

