### 5. No CORS policy (Medium — A05)

Without an explicit policy, you rely on browser defaults. Any future endpoint using custom headers, cookies, or non-simple methods will get surprise CORS behavior — and you risk accidentally enabling `*` with credentials.

**Recommendation:** explicit allowlist:

```js
