The app never calls `express.json()` / `express.urlencoded()`, and neither route reads `req.query`, `req.params`, or `req.body`. So there is literally no user input being processed today — meaning **no injection, SSRF, XSS, or deserialization vector actually exists in this file**. This will change the moment a route accepts input, so bake the defenses in now.

