`alice@example.com` / `bob@example.com` are RFC 2606 reserved example addresses, so not real PII. Still, `/users` unconditionally returns email addresses with **no authentication and no authorization** (OWASP A01 – Broken Access Control, A07 – Identification & Authentication Failures). If this endpoint is ever backed by a real user table, it becomes a mass-disclosure bug.

### 3. Missing security headers (OWASP A05 – Security Misconfiguration)
No `helmet()`. Responses will omit `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Content-Security-Policy`, etc.

