// Error handler — must have 4 args
app.use((err, req, res, _next) => {
  req.log?.error({ err }, 'unhandled');
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'internal_error' });
});
```

---

### 8. A05 — Hardcoded port / bind address, no config hygiene (Low)

`app.listen(3000, ...)` binds to all interfaces by default. In some deploy contexts you want to bind to a specific interface (e.g. behind a sidecar proxy only). Port should come from env.

**Fix:**
```js
