const host = process.env.HOST || '0.0.0.0'; // or '127.0.0.1' behind a proxy
app.listen(port, host, () => logger.info({ port, host }, 'listening'));
```

Also make sure your process manager / container sets `NODE_ENV=production`, which changes many defaults (Express view caching, `helmet` CSP behavior, etc.).

---

### 9. A08 — No graceful shutdown (Low)

Without SIGTERM handling, in-flight requests are killed on deploy, and the process can be evicted before draining. This is an integrity/availability issue more than a confidentiality one, but it belongs in a security review because abrupt termination can leave persistent state in inconsistent states.

**Fix:**
